Here is a guide for installing Git on different operating systems and checking its version:

Windows:
Download the Installer:

Go to the Git for Windows website.
Download the installer for Windows.
Run the Installer:

Run the downloaded .exe file.
Follow the installation wizard. The default settings are usually fine.
Verify Installation:

Open Command Prompt or PowerShell.

Check the version with:


git --version
Linux:
Install via Package Manager:

For Debian/Ubuntu-based systems:

sudo apt update
sudo apt install git
For Red Hat/CentOS-based systems:

sudo yum install git
For Fedora:

sudo dnf install git
For Arch Linux:

sudo pacman -S git
Verify Installation:

git --version
macOS:
Install via Homebrew (Recommended):

If you donot have Homebrew installed, install it first by following instructions at brew.sh.

Then, install Git with:

brew install git
Install via Xcode Command Line Tools:

Install the command line tools which include Git:

xcode-select --install
Verify Installation:

git --version
These commands and methods will help you install Git on your preferred operating system and check the version installed.